(h) to co-operate with the representative bodies of other professions and other institutions;
to co-operate with the representative bodies of other professions and other institutions;
(i) to promote research in the development of the law in general and particularly in relation to— (i) the applicability and suitability of received law; (ii) the character and content of customary law; (iii) the influence of industrial, commercial and technological development on society and social institutions;
