The Association shall have power, for the advancement of its objects or any of them—
(a) to acquire, hold, develop, sell, mortgage, charge, lease or otherwise deal with or dispose of property of all kinds, whether real or personal;
to acquire, hold, develop, sell, mortgage, charge, lease or otherwise deal with or dispose of property of all kinds, whether real or personal;
(b) to raise or borrow money in such manner and upon such security as may be determined by the Council.
to raise or borrow money in such manner and upon such security as may be determined by the Council.

(1) The funds of the Association shall consist of— (a) such sums as may be paid to the Association by way of entrance fees and subscriptions of members and fees payable on admission to the roll of practitioners and the issue of practising certificates; (b) such sums as may be paid to the Association by way of grant or donation; (c) such other moneys as may accrue to the Association in the exercise of its functions.
